description:
&lt;p&gt;In West Lancashire, Lancashire and South Cumbria NHS provides inpatient service for adults at The Scarisbrick Centre. The Centre has 22 beds across 2 wards and includes a 4 bed psychiatric intensive care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit provides assessment and interventions for clients, operates seven days a week and is accessible 24hrs per day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications from RMNs who are &lt;strong&gt;currently registered with the NMC with demonstrable experience&lt;/strong&gt;. A number of full and part time permanent contract opportunities for band 5 staff nurses have now arisen for the right candidates based at the Scarisbrick Centre in West Lancashire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated Staff nurses who can demonstrate excellent clinical and interpersonal qualities. The successful candidate must be willing to work in fast paced environment, have a positive outlook and ensure that delivering a quality service, which genuinely engages with service users, carers and other stakeholders, is a key priority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will be expected to rotate across the 2 ward footprint and be able to work shifts covering 24 hours, seven days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job share and flexible working arrangements are available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You may also be eligible for a Relocation Package or Golden Hello incentives (subject to confirmation). Apply now for further details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Moorcroft on 01695 684125&lt;/p&gt;
